:"Like his ancestor Burwell Newton, Henry struggled to make himself understood, and suffered lifelong insomnia from boyhood. An indomitable persistence carried him over both, and he became one of the foremost lawyers in Connecticut."},{"number":4,"category":"law","header":"Counsel to a bank and a presidential candidate","body":"His clients included the Yale National Bank, Brown Brothers of New York, and William Jennings Bryan in the matter of the Bennett will. He argued many causes before the courts of last resort and was much consulted by the public and the bar alike."}],"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["law","politics"],"notable_blurb":"Yale Law valedictorian; Connecticut legislator and jurist","primary_url":"https://libguides.ctstatelibrary.org/law/judge-attorney-biographies/n","primary_url_label":"Connecticut State Library"},"career":[{"role":"Attorney","organization":"New Haven bar","start_year":1872,"end_year":1914},{"role":"Referee in Bankruptcy","organization":"U.S. District Court (appt. Judge William K. Townsend)","start_year":1898,"end_year":1914},{"role":"State Representative","organization":"Connecticut General Assembly (Durham 1885; New Haven 1895)","start_year":1885,"end_year":1895},{"role":"Member, State Board of Health","organization":"Connecticut","start_year":null,"end_year":null}],"education":[{"institution_name":"Durham Academy","relationship":"student","degree":"Preparatory"},{"institution_name":"Wesleyan University","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1867-1870","degree":"A.B. 1870; Phi Beta Kappa, Eclectic Fraternity"},{"institution_name":"Yale Law School","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1870-1872","degree":"LL.B. 1872, valedictorian; prizes for best common-law and civil-law essays"}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"H00149","link_text":"Burwell Newton","display_label":"whose cleft-palate speech difficulty echoed four generations down"}],"slug":"henry-gleason-newton-1843"},"HD6449":{"id":"HD6449","